<h2 id="03-impacting-humanity">03. Impacting Humanity</h2>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p><strong>“I immediately think of one of the most famous maps of all time, Maximo Vignelli’s New York City subway map…“</strong> referenced Maximo Vignelli’s renowned design for the NYC subway map, learn more about this in this <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2012/08/06/arts/design/the-subway-map-that-rattled-new-yorkers.html">great New York Times article</a>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><strong>“The word “design” derives from designation…“</strong> learn more about the etymology here.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><strong>“I recall John Proctor’s famous line from Arthur Miller’s The Crucible…“</strong> watch Daniel Day Lewis as John Proctor deliver this line in a way only he can in Nicholas Hytner’s 1996 film adapation of the Crucible.</p>
  </li>
</ul>

